{"id":"math240-vareval2-growth001","cid":"MATH 240","topic":"Applications Growth Decay","subtopic":"Exponential growth and decay","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A radioactive substance decays. The amount Q(t) = {a}t^2 + {b} grams at time t seconds. Find Q({x_val}).","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":-5,"max":-1},"b":{"type":"int","min":50,"max":200},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":5}},"answer_expr":"vareval2","steps":["Q({x_val}) = {a}({x_val})^2 + {b} = {ax2} + {b} = {answer_vareval2} grams."],"tags":["ode","decay","model","evaluation"]}
